text: Gabukay () is a rural locality (an aul) and the administrative center of Gabukayskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 1811 as of 2018. There are 17 streets. == Geography == The aul is located on the left bank of the Pshish River, near the Ryazanskaya stanitsa. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Gabukay
